Text.Value: Soon.
Having fun with your new goblin friend? Bet you aren't.
It's fine, Memnos.
Please, leave us be. This isn't a good time -
Fighting chance? That's more than Kanon got.
First Kanon, now Memnos...
Bit of a fish in a barrel there. You could have given her a fighting chance.
Never mind, don't tell me. I want to picture it for myself.
It was a nice shot, if nothing else.
Let's hit the road, Memnos. I'm sick of this place.
It won't be my last.
It was wrong.
I've had some time to think since we last talked. Can't say I'm enjoying it much.

EditorData.NodeContext: Attempt at wry humor. Recovering from grief.

Text.Value: I need some time alone. Please.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still processing the loss of her friend and her attempt at revenge

Text.Value: I should've died with them.
It was justice. Or the start of it.
Leave.
This is my first kill.

EditorData.NodeContext: Processing the fact. In the next line, she'll be resolved to kill more goblins

Text.Value: That goblin won't be the last.
Heard you killed the goblin king. Did he suffer?

Synopsis: Arka and Memnos are idle in the druid grove after going to confront the captive goblin Sazza. The goblin may or may not have been killed in this prior scene. Arka remains bitter over the recent death of their friend, Kagha, while Memnos, if present, tries to shake her out of it.
